<paragraph blockId="5.[264,1325,284,1350]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis box="[312,431,1084,1109]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Diagnosis</emphasis>
This species differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[742,970,1084,1109]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Andesipolis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="masoni">
<emphasis box="[742,970,1084,1109]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Andesipolis masoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1026,1141,1084,1109]" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Andesipolis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="framea">
<emphasis box="[1026,1141,1084,1109]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">A. framea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to the long and curved ovipositor and the indistinct areola on the propodeum.
</paragraph>
